RelatedSentence: The Wright Amendment prevents Southwest from Dallas flying over nearby destinations like Albuquerque .
Officials at the Albuquerque International Sunport told Target 7 recently that they were preparing for the cuts .
The Sunport is working on ways to lower operating costs to offset the losses from Southwest .
The Sunport is working on ways to lower operating costs to offset the losses from Southwest .
Southwest makes up 58 percent of the Albuquerque International Sunport 's air traffic .
The Sunport makes money when Southwest leases space for gates , ticket counters and each time a flight lands .

Depending on travel season , the airline could cut up to 11 flights out of the Sunport .
